The visual of cracked cement has been one of meaning for me.  Over the years, I have watched its metaphorical meaning shift along with me.  Originally, the crack meant imperfection... something I sought to fix and smooth over.  When I started soul-searching and deepening my relationship with myself I realized a crack was an opening for growth.  A place for something to root and bloom.  Now, I see it as an opportunity to welcome in others to my garden.  Reminds me on the days I feel I make no progress just how much I have expanded.  You might not want Palmer's cracked pavement in your driveway 😉, but I am remaining open to receiving and welcoming in the new.
